    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Alpine ski racing for speed on a course marked by gates formed by paired poles, set at least 26 feet apart, through which the racer must pass. The racer who completes the course in the shortest time, without missing any gates or knocking down any poles, is the winner.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
